.TH "nlmclnt_lookup_host" 9 "nlmclnt_lookup_host" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nlmclnt_lookup_host \- Find an NLM host handle matching a remote server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct nlm_host *" nlmclnt_lookup_host
.BI "(const struct sockaddr *sap "  ","
.BI "const size_t salen "  ","
.BI "const unsigned short protocol "  ","
.BI "const u32 version "  ","
.BI "const char *hostname "  ","
.BI "int noresvport "  ","
.BI "struct net *net "  ","
.BI "const struct cred *cred "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sap" 12
network address of server
.IP "salen" 12
length of server address
.IP "protocol" 12
transport protocol to use
.IP "version" 12
NLM protocol version
.IP "hostname" 12
'\0'-terminated hostname of server
.IP "noresvport" 12
1 if non-privileged port should be used
.IP "net" 12
pointer to net namespace
.IP "cred" 12
pointer to cred
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns an nlm_host structure that matches the passed-in
[server address, transport protocol, NLM version, server hostname].
If one doesn't already exist in the host cache, a new handle is
created and returned.
